<TEXT>
an eastern airlines dc9 carrying 56 people left 
the runway tuesday night after being forced to return to the 
airport by hydraulic problems an airport spokesman said no 
injuries were reported 
eastern airlines flight 129 left the runway after the pilot 
began having trouble steering apparently because a tire blew said 
hartsfield atlanta international airport spokesman john braden 
the plane on a flight from atlanata to tallahassee fla with 
51 passengers and five crew members returned to the airport around 
1050 pm because of hydraulic problems braden said 
witnesses reported seeing sparks from the aircraft as it glided 
along the runway but braden said that was because the landing gear 
was scraping the runway 
he said the federal aviation administration and the national 
transportation and safety board would investigate the incident 
passengers were given the option of taking another flight out 
tuesday night or waiting until wednesday morning he said 
