<TEXT>
a fire killed a firefighter early today at a 
governmentfunded corporation that works on nuclear technology and 
authorities said political extremists may have set the blaze 
koichi fujita a 24yearold firefighter suffocated while 
battling the blaze on a basement floor of a ninestory building 
housing the power reactor and nuclear fuel development corp tokyo 
police reported 
police said the fire which also destroyed three cars owned by 
the corporation may have been started by a timeignition device 
set off by extremists who oppose nuclear projects 
a police official speaking on condition of anonymity said 
investigators found batteries and other metal debris apparently 
used for the device near the burned cars 
the corporation set up in 1967 handles the development of a 
fast breeder reactor and of a recycling technology on spent nuclear 
fuel 
it is also handling the development of technology to store 
nuclear waste at a facility under construction at a village in 
aomori 360 miles northeast of tokyo radical groups have opposed 
the project 
</TEXT>
