taken 217 people home free of charge since the nonprofit 
organization made its first run in october 1987 
the project evolved out of a small group of people who used to 
take the dead from the twin cities to reservations in personal 
vehicles as a kindness said john stone who coordinates the effort 
from indian family services in south minneapolis 
they would take them back in the back of a pickup truck or 
