the un security councils five permanent members 
have proposed an ambitious administrative role for the united 
nations in cambodia diplomats said today reporting progress 
toward ending the countrys civil war 
a communique released after two days of talks in paris appealed 
to cambodias warring factions to delegate all necessary powers 
to the un during a transitional period in which free elections 
would be organized 
under the proposal the four cambodian factions would jointly 
form a supreme national council that would occupy the countrys 
seat in the united nations but cede daytoday administrative 
responsibility to the un 
us diplomats said at a briefing today that the five permanent 
security council members the united states soviet union 
britain france and china had made significant progress 
