the man who led a 13month interim 
government after the us invasion of 1983 emerged today as 
grenadas likely new prime minister after parliamentary elections 
nicholas brathwaites centrist national democratic congress fell 
one seat short of a legislative majority in tuesdays balloting 
but most observers expected him to be able to persuade at least one 
legislator to switch to his party to form a government 
we have a situation where there will have to be negotiations 
which i would have preferred not to have brathwaite 64 said 
early today but at the same time i think it is not a difficult 
situation 
complete but unofficial results gave the national democratic 
congress seven of the 15 seats in the house of representatives 
grenadas parliament 
with one more seat brathwaite would have an eightseat majority 
and he held talks early today with other legislators about 
switching to his party 
the grenada united labor party of sir eric gairy the eccentric 
former prime minister deposed in a leftist coup in 1979 was second 
with four seats 
gairy 68 who dominated grenadas politics for nearly three 
decades before his ouster lost his bid for a parliamentary seat 
but his party with the second most legislators will likely form 
the official opposition and he could still play a role behind the 
scenes 
the national party of acting prime minister ben jones and the 
new national party led by keith mitchell a former cabinet 
minister won two seats each jones and mitchell were both returned 
to parliament 
the leftist maurice bishop patriotic movement failed to gain any 
parliamentary seats 
radio grenada said the results were complete but unofficial 
official results along with the popular vote totals were to be 
announced later today 
it was the second election since us troops along with a token 
regional force invaded the tiny caribbean island and toppled a 
marxist junta and there had been concern over the possible 
destabilizing effect of a gairy victory 
gairy the first prime minister after independence from britain 
in 1974 has been dogged by allegations of corruption and 
repression throughout his career as early as 1961 britain 
dissolved his preindependence government because of allegations of 
financial irregularities 
though nearly blind with glaucoma gairy had spoken of the 
possibility of a miracle cure and had declared his campaign 
divinely inspired 
the election happened to fall on the 11th anniversary of the 
marxist coup that toppled gairys authoritarian regime and brought 
to power bishops peoples revolutionary government 
bishop and 10 others were assassinated oct 19 1983 following a 
split in his government six days later the usled invasion 
force landed and evicted the junta that had seized power us 
officials said the invasion was necessary to protect american lives 
and prevent grenada from becoming a staging post for communist 
aggression in the region 
brathwaite an educator with no political experience at the 
time was called on to head the government during the 13month 
period between the invasion and the election in december 1984 
before the last election the reagan administration pressured 
three centrist parties to merge into the new national party led by 
the late prime minister herbert blaize mainly to block gairy 
blaize won 14 seats but the piecemeal party had disintegrated by 
the time of his death in december at the age of 71 
