province of thua thienhue on feb 22 when his hoe struck the 
usmade shell it detonated and sent the eggsize head into the 
farmers left arm 
in a report dated tuesday and seen in bangkok on wednesday the 
agency quoted explosives and ballistics experts as saying that it 
was too risky to tamper with the shell head as it might explode at 
the slightest displacement so immediate surgery was required 
the operation was performed feb 26 at a military hospital in 
the provincial capital of hue two surgeons volunteered for the 
job the news agency reported 
the head surgeon skillfully took the shell out of the victims 
arm and transfered it to a bomb disposal squad said the report 
it did not say where the shell came from but unexploded rounds 
left over from the vietnam war have killed or maimed many people in 
vietnam laos and cambodia since the fighting ended in 1975 
fierce bloody battles raged throughout hue the ancient 
imperial capital when the communists attacked and occupied the 
city in the pivotal tet offensive of early 1968 
