martin marietta corp today launched 
a powerful commercial rocket to boost a 140 million communications 
satellite into orbit but the uninsured satellite did not 
immediately signal that it was working 
the big titan 3 blasted off at 652 am est into a cloudy sky 
from the cape canaveral air force station 
intelsat the international communications company hoped for 
confirmation the satellite was working on its third expected pass 
over a tracking station on hawaii at about 11 am but no signal 
was confirmed said don oneal a spokesman for hughes aircraft 
co which built the satellite 
at midday the washington dcbased intelsat issued a brief 
statement saying that the satellite is encountering 
difficulties adding that company officials hoped to have more 
information later 
the north american aerospace command in colorado which tracks 
objects in space said it was asked by martin marietta to locate 
the satellite 
