which runs the program to suspend all ariane launches pending an 
investigation 
intelsat did not insure the satellite launched today ormsby 
said because the ariane explosion put already high insurance 
prices out of range 
the launch and satellite together cost an estimated 270 million 
intelsat a washington dcbased commercial cooperative of 118 
member nations owns and operates a global communications satellite 
system used by more than 170 countries todays launch is its 44th 
the first intelsat communications satellite was launched 25 years 
ago next month 
