and observed the workings of those government said he dreams of a 
new look for mongolia 
after a fiveyear period of transition and learning he 
predicted mongolia would have a parliamentary democracy with a 
presidential system like the united states that is the most 
effective and least costly way 
the economy would be dynamic exportoriented and ruled by 
market forces and mongolians would have heightened nationalism 
and selfesteem said the official who spoke on condition he not 
be identified 
