courseullessurmer france ap eight days after allied 
soldiers stormed ashore in normandy the destroyer la combattante 
carried gen charles de gaulle across the choppy gray english 
channel to a beach at courseullessurmer 
or was it next door at grayesurmer 
fortysix years later the communities still argue over whose 
sand bore the imprint june 14 1944 of the generals first 
footprint of the liberation 
the dispute has regained the stature of controversy in this 
special year of de gaulle the 100th anniversary of his birth the 
20th anniversary of his death and the 50th anniversary of his 
appeal of june 18 from london in 1940 urging the french to 
resist the german occupation 
a veterans group the normandy landing committee decided to 
commemorate the year by erecting a 60foothigh metal cross of 
lorraine de gaulle took the doublebarred cross as his personal 
symbol and it remains the symbol of gaullism 
for what the committee members called aesthetic reasons 
they decided to install the cross on grayes beach which enraged 
the folks at the courseulles city hall 
de gaulles own war memoirs are not much help 
on the morning of june 14 we cast anchor as near as possible 
to the french coast and landed together with a canadian regiment on 
the beach between the communities of courseulles and 
saintemereeglise he wrote courseulles and saintemereeglise 
are about 45 miles apart 
canadian soldiers liberated courseullessurmer and 
grayesurmer on dday june 6 1944 at one time or another de 
gaulle told officials of both towns he had fond memories of landing 
on their beach after four years in london 
im sure de gaulle himself did not know exactly where he set 
foot said remy simon a councilman assigned by courseulles mayor 
jeanlouis de mourgues to gather documents and build the case for 
their town which has about 3000 inhabitants 
in the end all this business is very painful said mayor 
michel grimaux of graye whose population is about 600 he hinted 
that courseulles interest was commercial as much as historic 
adding to the problem is the fact that no one in either town saw 
the general arrive for security reasons only military commanders 
were told in advance 
later on june 14 after giving a speech at bayeux de gaulle 
returned to courseulles and reboarded the destroyer there is no 
shortage of photographs of his departure from courseulles 
in 1946 de gaulle came back and he came back to 
courseulles said simon who has a footthick file of documents 
on the matter all of the eyewitnesses of the time confirm it was 
courseulles 
the courseulles documentation includes letters from several 
people who accompanied de gaulle including adm andre patou who 
was a captain at the time and skipper of la combattante and gen 
pierre koenig all say courseulles was the landing place 
we are fighting for the historical truth and thats all 
simon said he denied any other motives 
courseulles is a tourist town that grows to between 18000 and 
20000 people in summer and during school holidays it has a 
marvelous beach hotels swimming pools tennis stables and a 
chateau as well as a thriving oyster business and boatbuilding 
graye rich in charm has remained a sleepy country village 
mayor grimaux a boy of 12 at the time said his certainty that 
de gaulle landed in graye came from lt col wj humphrey a 
briton who was beachmaster on the grayecourseulles sector of the 
juno beach landing area 
according to grimaux humphrey said all vips to the newly 
liberated sectors of normandy including winston churchill and king 
george vi landed directly in front of the beachmasters 
headquarters which was clearly in graye it also was humphrey who 
provided de gaulle with a jeep the mayor said 
grimaux has clippings from the local newspaper in 1946 quoting 
de gaulle as telling a previous graye mayor i will never forget 
your community it is there that i landed 
la presse de calvados added editorially a decisive word that 
puts an end to certain controversies 
when a site was chosen for the lorraine cross the town boundary 
of courseulles was moved 65 yards west so the monument straddles it 
simon the courseulles councilman found that a grotesque 
solution but said we gave in to a compromise to be reasonable 
not because its right 
grimaux said all that interests me is the truth 
