<TEXT>
care famous for donating food digging canals 
and building hospitals in the third world has devised a new form 
of aid for the 1990s debt relief investment banking and venture 
capital 
the new yorkbased nonprofit organization has formed a 
subsidiary aimed at assisting heavily indebted developing countries 
devise innovative ways to reduce dependence on foreign loans 
cares small business assistance corp also can help foreign 
lenders recover some of the money they have sunk into latin america 
and other black holes of debt over the years subsidiary president 
donald nicholson said 
the subsidiary invests in small and mediumsized businesses 
from fruit canners in honduras to shrimp farmers in the 
philippines when invited by the host country it also is exploring 
business ventures in other countries undergoing profound political 
change including poland and nicaragua 
philanthropy and finance experts said the care subsidiary is the 
first investment banking venture formed by an international relief 
group to help developing countries become more selfreliant 
still with total third world foreign debt of 12 trillion 
cares effort is expected to have only a symbolic impact at first 
ive never heard of a relief group doing this said an 
official at the world bank in washington who asked not to be 
quoted by name but weve always said that anything helps any 
sensible approach with the interests of all parties at hand 
building small bridges is welcomed 
the care subsidiary will hold a minority stake in companies it 
invests in and will concentrate on businesses worth 250000 to 
25 million foreign banks and other creditors that contribute to 
the subsidiarys investment fund will receive dividends if the 
businesses are profitable 
were not going to solve the problems of heavily indebted 
third world countries nicholson said but we bring a unique 
approach to the third world crisis because were not for profit 
nicholson said he has talked with citibank chase manhattan bank 
and bankers trust about restructuring part of their third world 
debt through the care subsidiary 
he said cares clean reputation and cultural sensitivity in 
foreign countries give it advantages that larger forprofit 
companies might never obtain 
we are identifying existing viable businesses in the 
developing world and investing in them especially those that can 
earn hard currency through exports he said profits realized 
from this will be used to fund care development projects around the 
world 
the care venture coincides with economic shifts making it more 
difficult for developing countries to get aid from their 
industralized counterparts putting increased pressure on 
philanthropies and volunteer groups to fill the breach 
many large western banks for example burned by billions of 
dollars in bad loans to latin america are toughening terms for 
extending more credit the united states historically a leading 
source of aid to the developing world is becoming more stingy 
because of its large federal deficit 
a number of banks have sought to reduce third world debt 
exposure by converting some debt into local currency to be invested 
domestically others have tinkered with ways of repackaging or 
swapping debt for other types of securities such as the stock of a 
company based in a debtor country 
what care has done has in effect set up its own specific 
mechanism to carry out these type of transactions said peter j 
davies president and chief executive officer of interaction a new 
yorkbased coalition of 120 private voluntary relief organizations 
james mcdermott a banking analyst at the new york investment 
firm keefe bruyette amp woods said most major banks already have 
taken steps to protect themselves from third world loans but he 
said they are always looking at other ways to reduce the risk 
the whole process is chipping away at exposure he said 
this care subsidiary seems to be part of that process 
nicholson a 51yearold american raised in peru long has been 
active in third world investment banking he founded axion group a 
venture capital firm that invests in developing countries 
care the acronym for the cooperative for american relief 
everywhere inc is is one of the biggest international aid groups 
formed at the end of world war ii to send emergency supplies to 
refugees 
its 7200 employees and thousands of volunteers worldwide now 
distribute more than 300 million worth of aid annually 
</TEXT>
