but its efforts to curb inflation and shortages of key raw 
materials have reversed freemarket reforms of recent years once 
again miring foreign businessmen in socialist red tape 
moreover the conservative backlash to last years mass protests 
for democratic reform has revived official suspicion and resentment 
of foreigners 
theres a faction that believes the foreigners have been 
getting too good a deal and should be controlled said a western 
lawyer resident in shanghai speaking on condition of anonymity 
another lawyer said chinese bureaucrats told him they could not 
process foreign business quickly because theyre afraid of being 
seen as zhao ziyangs running dogs zhao was ousted in june as 
communist party chief blamed for excessive liberalism that helped 
spawn the democracy movement 
authorities sent one foreign company a letter admonishing it not 
to look for profit in china every penny you make as a foreign 
investor the chinese look at as a penny out of their pocket 
said a western diplomat 
several major american companies say they are thinking of 
pulling out were not here on a welfare basis said one 
american manager who did not want his company named before a 
decision is made 
he said efforts to mend problems with the chinese partner 
reminded him of a child trying to keep his parents together when 
maybe its the best thing for them to divorce 
another joint ventures foreign board members voted to dissolve 
the venture but the chinese side refused a small us familyowned 
company simply walked away in frustration from its china joint 
venture not bothering to formally dissolve ties 
new investment contracts have been signed since june when the 
army attack on student protesters in beijing chilled 
chineseforeign relations but they are down sharply from the 
prejune pace 
one problem is that government signals are confusing the 
national peoples congress chinas legislature is expected to 
amend the joint venture law to pledge not to nationalize them and 
to let foreigners to serve as chairmen 
businessmen call these positive moves but an even more welcome 
proposal to extend the 50year limit on the life of joint 
ventures faces stiff opposition and is not expected to pass 
the government also has tightened controls on joint venture 
prices imports and exports and purchases of domestic supplies 
treating them in the words of one foreign expert more and more as 
if they were stateowned companies 
shanghai volkswagen was still waiting in early march for beijing 
to decide its 1990 production quota and prices before last year 
it needed only shanghai city approval to change prices 
the new controls are not just from the center of power shanghai 
approved new regulations last year giving the communist 
partycontrolled unions the right to join in joint ventures 
longterm planning sessions and to intervene whenever a worker is 
disciplined or fired 
foreign businesses also have been hurt by last years dramatic 
slowdown in chinese economic growth accompanied by a dramatic cut 
in bank loans and severe shortage of cash for even normal 
transactions 
our accounts receivable have gone right out the window said 
the american manager of a shanghai joint venture weve sent 
teams out collecting i know of a company that sends two people to 
sit in debtors offices and tells them not to leave until they are 
paid 
some joint ventures have borrowed from foreign parent companies 
or from union funds or have mortgaged assets in what amounts to a 
handtomouth existence 
but local authorities equally desperate for funds have hit on 
the joint ventures like piggy banks 
seacliff limited for example a usjapanese partner in a new 
luxury hotel and office complex in shanghai has been told that for 
every car it imports for the hotel it will have to donate two cars 
to local authorities the centers general manager michael kalyk 
said the issue is under negotiation 
