cooperative gets a frustrated look when he talks about profits 
his credit union founded in 1986 as chinas first private 
banking operation earned 13 million yuan or about 276000 last 
year but after taxes it had 15300 left to distribute among 
shareholders 
we originally thought wed make more yang said but the 
number and size of taxes keep growing three more were added last 
year 
some wenzhou residents have adjusted to the change others have 
shut down to wait for bitter times more than half a million 
traveling salesmen have come home because of poor business ma said 
but wenzhous private business sector has by no means folded 
hundreds of openfront family shops still line the narrow 
streets their displays of shoes stylish clothes leather belts 
buttons and toys pushing onto the sidewalks 
a steady steam of tiny polishmade fiats navigate the streets 
with tinny horns beeping most with private businessmen at the 
wheel 
