<TEXT>
microsoft corp a computer software developer 
has declared a 100 percent stock dividend that amounts to a 
oneforone stock split 
microsoft said tuesday the new stock would be issued to 
shareholders of record march 26 doubling the number of shares 
outstanding to about 112 million 
microsoft stock closed tuesday at 10625 down 2 in 
overthecounter trading 
raymond b ferguson microsofts director of administration 
said it was the second dividend the company has declared since it 
went public in march 1986 the first also a 100 percent stock 
dividend was issued in september 1987 
its not common to have a cash dividend in our industry 
ferguson said there is a greater requirement for cash to 
continue to grow the business 
microsoft president jon shirley said the dividend was declared 
to make the stock more attractive to a broader range of investors 
scott mcadams an analyst with ragan and mackenzie inc in 
seattle said making the stock more affordable also could boost the 
value of current stock holdings in the long run 
the market tends to like nominally priced stocks mcadams 
said 
when prices get too high he said theres a little bit of a 
psychological edge operating there that may keep the value of the 
stock down a little bit 
microsoft reported a profit of 74 million or 125 a share on 
revenue of 300 million for the three months ended dec 31 
compared with profit of 47 million or 85 cents a share on 
revenue of 210 million for the same period a year earlier 
