<DOCNO> AP900314-0194 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the united states on wednesday unveiled a proposal 
to drastically reduce or eliminate import tariffs as its 
contribution to an ambitious international tradeliberalizing 
agreement planned for the end of the year 
us deputy trade representative rufus yerxa said the offer was 
contingent on the united states receiving corresponding concessions 
from its trading partners in the 96nation general agreement on 
tariffs and trade 
in an 800page document to be submitted to gatt members on 
thursday the united states proposes the elimination of tariffs on 
imported agricultural products 
for a second group of goods including wood products and paper 
steel aluminum certain chemical products and selected 
construction equipment it proposes dutyfree access to us 
markets provided trading partners remove tariffs and all trade 
barriers from matching us exports 
for all other products the us proposal allows for tariff 
reductions up to a maximum of 50 percent again subject to 
reciprocal concessions by other countries after bilateral talks 
this third category includes the sensitive us textiles sector 
traditionally protected by high import tariffs 
yerxa told a press conference that cuts in textile duties were 
unlikely to reach the 50 percent ceiling although this was 
theoretically possible under the us plan 
textiles is a very tough category for us to make concessions 
on he said 
despite high import duties in sectors such as textiles clothing 
and footwear the united states has a low overall level of tariffs 
a tariff or tax levied on imported goods is one of the main ways 
of shielding domestic industry from foreign competition because it 
makes imported goods more expensive and therefore less competitive 
than domestic products 
yerxa said us import duty levels averages 66 percent for 
agricultural products and 5 percent for industrial goods in 
contrast to much higher protection in other countries 
in brazil for example tariffs average 47 percent of the value 
of traded goods according to figures listed in the us document 
in india the average is 99 percent and in pakistan 106 percent 
it would be a great travesty for the united states to have to 
reduce its already low tariffs if others dont make reductions 
yerxa said 
at a meeting in montreal in december 1988 trade ministers agreed 
on the overall target of 33 percent for tariff cuts 
a deal reached in january allowed gatt members to select their 
own method of achieving this target proposals have to be submitted 
by thursday 
gatt is a multilateral trade agreement first established in 1947 
and designed to establish rules reduce tariffs and provide a 
setting for a solution to international trade problems members of 
the marketorientated organization account for more than 
fourfifths of world trade 
the current uruguay round of trade talks is expected to end in 
december with an ambitious new agreement to liberalize trade in 
areas such as agriculture and textiles 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

