<TEXT>
early march sales of cars and light trucks made 
by the nations big three automakers dipped 68 percent compared 
with slow sales a year ago the companies said wednesday 
general motors corp ford motor co and chrysler corp said 
they sold cars and light trucks at an average daily rate of 27289 
during the march 110 period this year compared with 29281 during 
the same time last year 
car sales fell 77 percent and truck sales were down 54 
percent 
march and april usually usher in a more bouyant car and truck 
buying season as americans shake off the winter and take to the 
highways 
but incentives offered during january and february of last year 
had attracted wouldbe march and april buyers depressing the sales 
rate for the latter two months 
the march 1989 sales rate was the lowest during the first nine 
months of the year sales hit the skids during the final three 
months of last year but the pace picked up slightly after the 
first of the year 
despite comparison with a slow sales period a year ago early 
march sales were lower this year 
through march 10 of this year the car and truck selling rate 
was running 26 percent behind last years rate car sales were off 
56 percent but truck sales were up 22 percent mainly because of 
strong chrysler minivan sales in january 
chrysler said its early march car and truck sales were running 
113 percent behind last years pace with car sales down 91 
percent and truck sales off 134 percent 
but for the year chryslers car and truck sales were running 
02 percent ahead of last year with car sales down 69 percent and 
truck sales up 68 percent 
ford said its early march car sales were down 81 percent and 
truck sales were down 31 percent combining for a 61 percent 
sales decrease from yearago levels for the year fords vehicle 
sales were running 65 percent behind last year with car sales 
down 86 percent and truck sales down 35 percent 
gms combined car and truck sales for early march was down 57 
percent compared with last year as car sales fell 71 percent and 
truck sales dropped 31 percent so far this year gms car sales 
were down 32 percent and truck sales were up 47 percent 
combining for a sales rate 07 percent below last year 
