<TEXT>
prudential insurance co of america said 
wednesday that its 1989 profit slipped 10 percent from a year 
earlier due largely to two major acquisitions that expanded its 
real estate and securities businesses 
meanwhile the head of its prudentialbache securities inc 
subsidiary disclosed there would be layoffs later this year in 
response to the sluggishness on wall street 
george ball prudentialbache chairman and chief executive 
officer did not specify the number of jobs that would be cut but 
said the firm wanted to avoid the bludgeon approach 
prudential said losses in its securities and residential real 
estate operations were largely to blame for a drop in 1989 earnings 
to 743 million from 829 million the previous year revenue 
however rose 15 percent to 4303 billion from 3750 billion 
prudential which is a mutual insurance company said income 
from operations before policyowner dividends and income taxes 
totaled 356 billion in 1989 down from 371 billion in 1988 
the company said it had solid earnings gains in its insurance 
and asset management businesses 
the losses in its securities and real estate businesses came 
mainly from prudentials acquisition last year of merrill lynch amp 
cos residential real estate operations and the branch offices of 
the wall street firm thomson mckinnon inc 
at its annual media briefing prudential chairman robert c 
winters called the approximatley 300 million real estate 
acquisition the most significant strategic development for the 
company last year prudential currently has more than 900 brokerage 
offices with nearly 25000 sales associates in 40 states 
winters said the thomson mckinnon acquisiton would position 
the firm to take full advantage of the potential we see down the 
road for the securities industry 
right now individual investors are staying away from the 
marketplace winters said we believe ultimately this period 
will end its a cyclical business 
several wall street firms including shearson lehman hutton 
inc have been contracting in recent months in part because of the 
slowdown since the 1987 stock market crash and a decline in mergers 
and acquisitions due to a sharp decline in the junk bond market 
ball who also spoke at the annual briefing said 
prudentialbache was evaluating where future staff cuts would be 
made the firm currently has around 19000 employees 
i do expect our head count to be lower he told reporters 
prudentialbache recorded a net loss of 51 million in 1989 
compared with a 111 million profit the previous year 
in its individual insurance sector prudential posted a 4 
percent increase in new business premiums to 34 billion life 
insurance sales slipped 15 percent to 806 million but annuity 
sales rose 23 percent to 21 billion it said 
new property and casualty insurance sales were up 23 percent to 
342 million but earnings were hurt by hurricane hugo and the san 
francisco earthquake it said 
the group insurance earnings also improved prudential said 
premium and fees from new sales of group life and health coverages 
were up 23 percent to 2 billion 
prudential said its institutional asset management group which 
manages a wide range of investments for pension funds and other 
large institutional investors had an 88 percent decline in sales 
to 78 billion 
