<TEXT>
general motors corp on wednesday recalled about 
147200 cars and vans in five separate actions for problems that 
include the possibility of parts breaking in rear suspensions of 
some corvettes 
the recall included 46000 1988 and 1989model corvettes with 
rearwheel tie rod assemblies that may break causing a loss of 
control 
gm spokesman tom pyden said the automaker wasnt aware of any 
deaths or major injuries because of any of the problems 
the automaker also recalled 
about 1100 1990model pontiac grand prix se turbo cars for 
removal of a rear spring heat shield which may puncture the fuel 
tank in a collision 
about 84000 198789 chevrolet corsica sedans because of door 
hinge problems which could affect the cars ability to withstand a 
sideimpact crash 
about 10000 1990 buick riviera and cadillac eldorado and 
seville cars with potentially sticky rear shoulder safety belt 
assemblies 
nearly 6100 198789 chevrolet and gmc step vans built for 
commercial delivery for replacement of a seat pedestal which may 
not be able to hold the seat or a passenger during a crash 
gm said owners were being notified by mail inspections and 
repairs will be performed for free 
